<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Calls For Greater Electronic-Information Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Premier Li Peng told a
national conference on the electronics industry in Guangdong
Province's Zhaoqing city that China should give priority to
developing its electronic-information industry.
</P>
<P>
The industry has played a very important role in the country's
socialist modernization drive, he said, calling on people in the
industry to hold the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory high, to
increase reforms, open up wider, speed up the restructuring, and
increase the ability to develop new products.
</P>
<P>
According to Hu Qili, minister of electronics industry, China's
electronic-information industry had rapid growth in 1997, with 250
billion yuan in sales.
</P>
<P>
The industry had a 13 percent growth in profits, exports, and
added value goods in 1997, and PCs, programmable exchanges, and
color television sets were produced in large quantity in keeping
with market needs.
</P>
<P>
State-owned electronics companies increased restructuring
efforts through mergers and re-organization, and the industry
structure was improved somewhat last year.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that, in 1998, the industry will grow at about 20
percent to provide a sound foundation for development in the next
century.
</P>
<P>
This year, it will focus on developing digital and network
products, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
