<HEADLINE> Six Nepalese Killed in Traffic Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Six persons were killed and
20 others injured early Tuesday morning when a night bus fell 50
feet from the road in Dadeldhura district of far western Nepal,
the official RSS news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Five passengers were killed on the spot, while another died on
the way to hospital, the RSS said.
</P>
<P>
Among the injured, seven are still undergoing treatment with
two in critical condition, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident is not known yet, it added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
