<HEADLINE> China Sets New Oil, Gas Production Goals For 1998 (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- China plans to produce 143
million tons of crude oil and 16.5 billion cu m of natural gas
from land wells this year and verify 600 million tons of oil
reserves and 50 billion cu m of gas.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yongkang, president of of the China National Petroleum
Corp (CNPC), told a national meeting that steps will be taken to
stabilize oil production in the East and to explore the West,
placing equal emphasis on oil and gas production.
</P>
<P>
Exploration will be given top priority this year to increase
oil reserves and oil output. Existing oilfields in the eastern
part of China will try to maintain their present production
level, and the western areas will work even harder to increase oil
and gas production.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said the Daqing Oilfield will expand its oil production
scale, speed up oil exploration in new areas and ensure an output
of 56 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The Shengli Oilfield in Shangdong Province will increase
exploration this year and try to slow decreases in production to
maintain an annual oil output of 28 million tons.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980114.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's New Oil, Gas Production Goals for 1998 (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Liaohe Oilfield in northeastern China will work hard to
hold output at 15 million tons, and the Jilin Oilfield will
enlarge production capacity and plans to produce 3.8 million tons
of crude oil this year. The Huabei, Dagang, Zhongyuan, and Jidong
oilfields will try to find new oil reserves and make sure that oil
production will be stable or grow.
</P>
<P>
High hopes are being placed on exploration and development in
western areas and these are expected to become important oil
production bases for future oil production.
</P>
<P>
The Xinjiang and Changqing oilfields in western China will
increase oil exploration and reserves this year, and will produce
8.7 million tons and 3.2 million tons of oil, respectively. The
Tarim Oilfield is expected to produce 4.4 million tons of oil, a
1.3-million-ton increase from 1997. The Turpan-Hami Oilfield is
likely to find new oil reserves and will produce three million
tons of oil this year, according to Zhou.
</P>
<P>
Natural gas exploration and development will focus on Sichuan,
Shaanxi, and Gansu provinces, and the Ningxia Hui and Xinjiang
Uygur autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
This year will see rapid development of gasfields in northern
Shaanxi and Sichuan provinces, with a production capacity of 1.5
billion cu m and 2 billion cu m, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
