<HEADLINE> Russian Premier's Helicopter Makes Emergency Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A helicopter with Russian First
Deputy Premier Boris Nemtsov on board made an emergency landing
near Torzhok Tuesday morning, according to Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was en route to Valdai. The emergency landing was
made at about 10:30 a.m. Moscow time, about 12 kilometers away
from Torzhok, when a fire alarm from one of the helicopter's
engines was activated.
</P>
<P>
After the landing, however, no trace of a fire could be
found. The helicopter was grounded until the source of the problem
was discovered and all the problems were investigated and
eliminated.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was also carrying Russian presidential press
secretary Sergei Yastrzhembsky, presidential aide Vladimir
Shevchenko, president Boris Yeltsin's daughter Tatyana Dyachenko
and her son. 
</P>
