<HEADLINE> Germany Provides Humanitarian Aid to Quake Victims in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The German government Tuesday
announced to provide 75,000 marks (about 41,000 U.S. dollars) in
emergency humanitarian aid for victims of a strong earthquake which
struck north China on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's earthquake measuring 6.2 on the Richter scale struck
the Zhangbei and Shangyi counties north China's Hebei Province,
killing at least 47 people and damaging 103,000 houses.
</P>
<P>
The German foreign ministry said that the German aid would be used
to re-build houses for earthquake victims to help them survive the
severe winter season. 
