<DOCNO> XIE19980114.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> WHO Team to Review Influenza Surveillance in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A team of experts will visit
Guangdong and Hong Kong to review ongoing influenza surveillance
activities there at the invitation of the government of the
People's Republic of China, the World Health Organization (WHO)
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in southern China from January 16 to 22, the
experts will review epidemiological and virological surveillance
for influenza in the region, said WHO in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The visit forms part of WHO's efforts to strengthen influenza
surveillance in humans and animals in the Western Pacific region,
it said.
</P>
<P>
The team will be in Beijing on January 23 to discuss with the
Chinese government means of strengthening the national plan of
action for the surveillance and control of influenza.
</P>
<P>
China's influenza surveillance system is already integrated
into the global WHO influenza surveillance program.
</P>
<P>
The team will consist of influenza experts, virologists and
epidemiologists from the WHO headquarters, the WHO Regional Office
for the Western Pacific, two WHO Collaborating Centers for
Influenza, and representatives of the US-Japan Task Force on
communicable disease control. 
</P>
</TEXT>
