<HEADLINE> Tourism up in Vietnam's capital in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese capital Hanoi's
tourist sector received 1.2 million visitors in 1997, 14 percent
more than that of in 1996, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The tourist sector has brought in a revenue of 1,062 billion
vietnamese dong (about 86.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Hanoi now has 140 travel agencies and 350 hotels with 73,402
rooms, more than 6,000 of which meet the international standards.
</P>
<P>
Hanoi is expected to reach a growth rate of 15-18 percent in
1998 by opening more domestic and foreign tours and improving
services. 
</P>
