<HEADLINE> Zambia Ready to Boost Trade With Congo (K) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Minister Rell Walubita
today said Zambia is ready to boost trade with the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DPC) for the mutual benefits of the two
peoples and countries, Zambia News Agency ZANA reported.
</P>
<P>
Opening the 9th session of the Joint Permanent Commission
between Zambia and DPC here, Walubita said the two countries are
also to improve their transport and communication links in order
to enhance trade.
</P>
<P>
Zambia's is willing to assist the reconstruction of the
Congolese economy by providing Kinshasa with technical assistance
in various fields, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Referring to a commercial bank which Zambia has pledged to
open in DPC this year, Walubita said the establishment of the
bank would promote trade and monetary payments for trade between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He called on the permanent commission to create an enabling
environment for the consolidation and promotion of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the same occasion, Congolese Foreign Minister
Bizima Karaha urged the commission to find ways of eradicating
smuggling and illicit trade between the two countries, which are
a hindrance to trade development.
</P>
<P>
Karaha stressed that meaningful trade should be promoted along
the border when the problem of smuggling is brought under
control. 
</P>
