<HEADLINE> Vietnam Returns American MIA's Remains to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam Tuesday returned some
remains of american servicemen listed as missing in action (MIA)
during the Vietnam War to the U.S., Vietnam News Agency (VNA)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The handing over was witnessed by visiting U.S. senator John
Kerry and U.S. ambassador to Vietnam Douglas Peterson.
</P>
<P>
The remains, excavated by joint search teams during the 48th joint
search for MIAs or collected unilaterally by the Vietnamese side, were
examined in Hanoi by Vietnamese and American forensic specialists.
</P>
<P>
It is the 67th times that Vietnam has returned MIA's remains to
the U.S. since 1973, said VNA..
</P>
<P>
The U.S. government representative expressed thanks and high
appreciation to the Vietnamese government and people for their
humanitarian and effective cooperation on the issue, the VNA said.
</P>
