<HEADLINE> France Expresses Regret Over Iraq's New Blocking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 13 (Xinhua) -- France today expressed regret
over the decision of the Iraqi government to block a United
Nations arms inspection team (UNSCOM) headed by an American from
carrying out its mission.
</P>
<P>
"France deeply regrets the decision of the Iraqi authorities
which counters the U.N. Security Council resolutions giving the
UNSCOM the unconditional right to send to Iraq all inspectors,"
said French Foreign Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
Iraq stopped a UNSCOM team from working Monday because it was
headed by former U.S. marine officer Scott Ritter and because it
consisted of too many American and British inspectors.
</P>
<P>
France asked Iraq to "re-consider" the decision and allow the
inspectors to resume their work. 
