<HEADLINE> UK Issues Statement on Iraqi Move Against UNSCOM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The British government
criticized here today Iraq for halting a mission of the United
Nations arms inspectors, saying "Iraqi claims of bias are clearly
false."
</P>
<P>
British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said in a statement issued
this afternoon, "It is for the Executive Chairman of UNSCOM
(United Nations Special Commission on Iraq), not Iraq, to dictate
the composition of the inspection teams."
</P>
<P>
The Iraqi government announced Monday that it would bar an
inspection team headed by an American and warned that the
suspension would remain in effect until the composition of the
team is changed.
</P>
<P>
"The present round of inspection is being carried out by 44
personnel from 17 countries. Iraqi claims of bias are clearly
false," Cook said.
</P>
<P>
The foreign secretary said that his government would discuss
"the latest position with its EU (European Union) partners."
</P>
<P>
"The EU strongly supports the insistence of the UN Security
Council that Iraq should implement its resolutions scrupulously,"
the statement added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
