<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-13 17:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey, Northern Cyprus Sign Cooperation Protocol </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Turkey and northern Cyprus
Tuesday signed a protocol to elevate political and economic
consultation, Turkey's Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The protocol was signed in the Turkish Cypriot-controlled part
of Nicosia by northern Cyprus' "Foreign and Defense Minister"
Taner Etkin and Turkish Foreign Ministry Undersecretary Korkmaz
Haktanir.
</P>
<P>
It foresees establishment of political and economic
consultation committees which will convene at the level of
"ministers and undersecretaries," according to the report.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, the Turkish official said northern
Cyprus should be recognized as an "independent and democratic
state" in the world, adding that the installation of peace and
stability in eastern Mediterranean depends on that.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriots declared a "Turkish Republic of Northern
Cyprus" in 1983, which is recognized only by Turkey, the
political, economic and military supporter of those Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into Greek Cypriot-dominated south and
Turkish Cypriot-controlled north since 1974 when Turkish troops
landed and took over the northern third of the island in the wake
of an abortive coup seeking union with Greece. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
