<HEADLINE> Grenade Blast Kills 6 in N. Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed and
13 others injured when a hand-grenade went off accidentally in
Gondar of northern Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency today quoted local police as saying
that the accident occurred last weekend when a person who was
trying to calm the bickering between a couple fell down as the
hand-grenade he was holding went off at the spot.
</P>
<P>
Five people, including the one holding the hand-grenade, were
instantly killed and another died in a hospital where he was sent
for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Three people are taken into custody for investigation whereas
two others wanted in connection with the incident are still at
large, according to the local police. 
</P>
</TEXT>
