<HEADLINE> Iraqi Trade Minister Meets Russian Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Trade Minister Mohammed
Mehdi Saleh today met with visiting Vice Chairman of the Russian
Liberal Democratic Party Ghotsrev and his accompanying delegation,
the Iraqi news agency INA reported.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Saleh expressed Iraq's keenness to expand
economic and trade cooperation with Russia, saying that Russian
companies would be given priority to conclude contracts with Iraq
within the Iraqi-U.N. oil-for-food program.
</P>
<P>
Iraq announced last week that it was ready to conclude
contracts after U.N. chief Kofi Annan approved its food
distribution plan under the third phase of the oil-for-food deal.
</P>
<P>
Ghotsrev said his country would fulfill all its commitments
toward the contracts it had signed with Iraq within the second
phase of the oil-for-food deal and in a way that would help
alleviate the sufferings of the Iraqi people.
</P>
<P>
Russian companies are seeking new contracts for the export of
foodstuffs to Iraq and the purchase of Iraqi oil, he said.
</P>
<P>
Under the oil-for-food deal, Iraq is allowed to export 2
billion U.S. dollars worth of oil to buy food, medicine and other
humanitarian supplies for its people.
</P>
<P>
Ghotsrev said that the Russian Liberal Democratic Party would
continue its effort to help lift the embargo on the Iraqi people,
adding that a number of its party members would take direct
flights between Moscow and Baghdad in February and March to
extend medical aid to the Iraqi people and convey a number of the
Iraqi sick for treatment in Russian hospitals.
</P>
<P>
With the approval of the U.N., a Russian Liberal Democratic
Party delegation flew to Iraq at the end of last year on board a
plane carrying 5 tonnes of medicines for Iraqi children on
board. This was the first foreign civil flight to the country
since 1991 when the U.N. imposed sanctions and a travel ban on
Iraq against its invasion of Kuwait. 
</P>
</TEXT>
