<HEADLINE> Greece Plans to Clear Thousands of Landmines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Greece will begin this year to
remove thousands of landmines in the Grammos mountain region on
the northern part of the country.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia-Thrace Minister Philipos Petsalnikos said today that
the Greek government intended to turn the region into a tourist
destination.
</P>
<P>
He said that funds from the third community support framework
and the Greek National Defense Ministry have already been
allocated for the project.
</P>
<P>
The landmines, which were laid in the region during the
1947-1949 civil war between communist-backed resistance fighters
and allies-backed troops, have left dozens of people dead and many
more injured in the past years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
