<HEADLINE> Greece, Poland Agree on Strengthening Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Greece and Poland today decided
to step up the level of their contacts politically and
economically.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made during the talks between Greek Alternate
Foreign Minister George Papandreou and his Polish counterpart,
Andrej Ananicz.
</P>
<P>
During the talks, the Greek side agreed to help Poland in its
efforts to join the European Union, which had last month decided
to include Warsaw in its first wave of expansion.
</P>
<P>
Currently, some 30 Greek and joint Greek-Polish enterprises are
reportedly active in Poland, especially in commerce and the fur,
marble and farming goods sectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
