<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Botswana Central Bank Lowers Interest Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Botswana
today announced a reduction of the bank rate by 0.5 percentage
points to 12 percent, effective immediately, South African Press
Association reported.
</P>
<P>
The bank said it was making the move to stimulate additional
productive economic activity, encourage public savings and to
make the country more attractive to foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
Botswana is among the fast growing economies in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The bank said it was opportune to signal lower nominal
interest rates since it believed that inflation should be kept in
check.
</P>
<P>
Botswana's year-on-year inflation had dropped to a 10-year low
of 7.8 percent at the end of December, compared to 9.1 percent in
January 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
