<HEADLINE> Kenya to Conduct National Demographic Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The National Council for
Population and Development (NCPD) is scheduled to conduct a
national demographic and health survey in the entire country this
year, according to a Kenya News Agency report today.
</P>
<P>
The official agency said that the survey code-named KDHS-III
was aimed at collecting vital data to be used in the preparation
for future national development plans.
</P>
<P>
Key questions to be addressed during the survey will include
the number of children per family, family planning acceptance and
practice, where family planning services were obtained and time
and cost used by people to reach health facilities.
</P>
<P>
In order to conduct the survey, the council will organize a
three-week training course for personnel in Nakuru, some 160
Kilometers northwest Nairobi, beginning from January 19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
