<HEADLINE> 24 Insurgents Killed in Northern Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan government army
killed 24 armed insurgents in clashes that took place in northern
Ruhengeri prefecture today, military sources told Rwanda News
Agency (RNA).
</P>
<P>
The clashes occurred in the villages of Bisate in Kinigi
commune, and Shingiro in neighboring Mukingo commune, the sources
further indicated.
</P>
<P>
"Operations to flush out criminals out of Ruhengeri are
continuing," the army spokesman, Major Emmanuel Ndahiro said on
Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
According to Ndahiro, the government army acting on tips by
local residents intercepted a large group of armed "Interahamwe"
militiamen, and in the ensuing fighting that lasted only a few
hours, the army killed 24 assailants and charged some assault
rifles.
</P>
<P>
"There was no casualty on our side," Ndahiro pointed out,
adding that one of the insurgents has been captured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
