<DOCNO> XIE19980114.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK's Unelected Lords to Lose Power of Voting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Lords in the upper
House will be stripped of their privilege of voting in the House
of Lords, a government official said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A committee, charged with reforming the upper House, has
planned to remove the right to vote from Lords who have inherited
their seats.
</P>
<P>
"Removing the voting rights of hereditary peers was the first
thing the committee discussed and legislation will be drawn up
during this parliament," the government official was quoted by
Reuter as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The primary aim of the committee is to remove voting rights
and the inbuilt Conservative Party majority and try and make the
House of Lords more representative," the official said.
</P>
<P>
The plan was part of Prime Minister Tony Blair who has forced
the pace of constitutional change in his 8-1/2 months in power to
build a new Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980114.0072 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Producer Inflation Falls in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 13 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's
year-on-year producer price index for last November dropped to
4.7 percent, further down from the 26-year low of 4.9 percent in
last October, the Central Statistical Services (CSS) said today.
</P>
<P>
The monthly increase in the index was 0.3 percent against the
0.2 percent for October 1997, the South African Press Association
quoted CSS as saying.
</P>
<P>
The monthly growth resulted from fluctuations in the price
indices of petroleum and coal products, metal products transport
equipment and electricity.
</P>
<P>
The annual increase in the PPI for locally produced goods slid
to 5.3 percent, the lowest since 1972, the CSS said. This was 0.4
percentage points down from the corresponding annual rate of 5.7
percent in October.
</P>
<P>
Imports witnessed a higher annual rate with a rise of 2
percent in November, compared with the 1.3 percent in October.
</P>
<P>
Economists said that the 4.7 percent year-on-year growth was
higher than their forecast of 4.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
They predicted that the year-on-year PPI growth for December
1997 would decline further to 4.4 percent, and the average 1998
production inflation ould drop by nearly one percentage point to
6.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
