<HEADLINE> Liaoning Beat Jiangsu in Chinese Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Liaoning Hunters beat MVP Hu
Weidong-led Jiangsu Nangang 83-72 in the 15th round of the Chinese
Basketball League on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Hu, who was voted the most valuable player of the Hilton
basketball league in the last two seasons, scored only 16 points
before the strong defence of the Liaoning squad.
</P>
<P>
James Lee, winner of the dunking test during the All-star game
last season, led Jiangsu with 24 points.
</P>
<P>
Three players from Liaoning scored double-digit points, with
Chinese national Wu Naiqun netting 20. Li Xiaoyong and Guo
Shiqiang added 18 points apiece.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning now stands third place with 11 wins and four losses,
with Jiangsu at sixth with nine wins and six losses.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Army continued their momentum by routing Beijing
Shougang 88-77, remaining atop the standings with only one defeat.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, Shenyang Army beat Sichuan Pandas
87-65, Jinan Army ousted Lianhang Airforce 88-83, Shanghai
Oriental defeated Zhejiang Zhongxin 61-50, Guangdong Hongyuan
outplayed Shandong Baoyuan 97-85. 
</P>
</TEXT>
