<HEADLINE> State of Emergency Over in Ottawa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian capital city of
Ottawa is beginning to return to normal following the worst snow
and ice storm in decades.
</P>
<P>
With power back on-line in most places, schools opened
Wednesday and federal public servants were back on the job.
</P>
<P>
The state of emergency was formally lifted in Ottawa on
Tuesday. But it is still in effect in some of the surrounding
townships. About 71,000 homes and businesses in these and other
townships in the eastern part of Ontario province were still
without power by late Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
It may take days, or even weeks for Ontario Hydro to restore
power to all its customers in the hardest-hit areas, Hydro
officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
