<HEADLINE> Philippines, Belgium Sign Investment Promotion Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines and Belgium
signed an agreement on reciprocal promotion and protection of
investments Wednesday to strengthen economic cooperation between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed here by Philippine Trade and Industry
Secretary Cesar Bautista and visiting Belgian Vice Prime Minister
and Minister of Finance Philippe Maystadt and witnessed by
Philippine President Fidel Ramos.
</P>
<P>
Maystadt said the agreement is a signal that the Belgian
business community maintains confidence on the Philippines despite
the current financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
In their meeting earlier, Ramos and Maystadt discussed ways to
promote bilateral ties between the two countries and ways to cope
with current currency crisis in East Asia.
</P>
<P>
Ramos agreed with Maystadt, who is on a two-day working visit
to the Philippines, that Asian nations need a "second line of
defense" to protect their economies.
</P>
<P>
Maystadt called for international solidarity to quickly solve
the financial meltdown because "this is not only a problem of this
region but the problem of the whole world."
</P>
<P>
The monetary problem has stalked the Asian region with
currencies of Thailand, Indonesia, Malaysia and the Philippines
tumble like dominos since July last year.
</P>
<P>
Trade between the Philippines and Belgium reached 400 million
U.S. dollars last year, according to the Department of Trade and
Industry.
</P>
<P>
Belgium has been engaged in small and medium enterprises in the
country and Belgian companies are keen to invest in bigger
projects like information technology, infrastructure and silver
ware. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
