<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE market Loses 30.93 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 14 (Xinhua)-- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday lost 30.93 points to
3400.79 as against Tuesday's close of 3431.72.
</P>
<P>
The national index downed by 10.23 points to 1482.80 from
previous close of 1493.03.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and US dollar index were quoted down at 333.60 and
138.23 compared with previous close of 335.32 and 139.95
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Speculative once again met with a strong resistance almost
erasing Tuesday's sensitive index gains on the stock market in the
wake of heavy selling pressure from bear operators as well as
foreign funds.
</P>
<P>
Operators have taken very serious view of reports that Japan's
financial problems had been pushing its economy into more
difficulties in the light of unstable situation in South-East
Asian stocks and currency markets.  
</P>
