<HEADLINE> Former Khmer Rouge Commander Shot Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, January 14 (Xinhua) -- A former Khmer Rouge
commander who defected to the government was shot dead Tuesday
after resisting arrest, a senior military official said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Phon Pheap, a former body-guard to the notorious Khmer Rouge
leader Pol Pot, was shot by military police on Tuesday night in
Somraung Tong district, Kompong Speu province, about 30 kilometers
from Phnom Penh.
</P>
<P>
According to officials, Pheap was escorting a shipment of
untaxed goods from Sihanoukville to Phnom Penh when police tried
to stop him.
</P>
<P>
Pheap reportedly resisted arrest and ran two roadblocks before he
was finally stopped. Pheap then opened fire on the police, killed one,
injured another and destroyed a car before he was shot and killed.
</P>
<P>
A friend of Pheap's reportedly said he received a call on
Tuesday night claiming that he (Pheap) had been arrested. The
friend said Pheap requested he bring food to him because he was
hungry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
