<HEADLINE> mee011410hke - Avalanche Claims 22 Lives in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 14 (Xinhua) - An avalanche buried a bus and two
other vehicles near the capital Tehran Tuesday night, killing 22
people and injuring 40 others, the official news agency IRNA
reported today.
</P>
<P>
IRNA quoted a security forces official as saying that the
incident happened on the Haraz road, near the town of Roudehen on
the southern slope of the Albroz range, 35 kilometers east of
Tehran.
</P>
<P>
No details were given about the incident, but the report said
that over 200 minor avalanches occurred the same night on the same
road linking the capital with the religious city of Mashad in the
east.
</P>
<P>
Heavy snow hit most areas of Iran in recently days as a
blizzard swept eastward, causing lots of traffic incidents and
forcing the authorities to close schools. 
</P>
