<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Produce 51-53 Million Tons of Unhusked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government
predicted that unhusked rice production in the 1997/98 planting
season will reach some 51 million to 53 million tons, an increase
of about 4 to 7 percent from last year's 49.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
"To date, some 2.6 million hectares of rice fields had been
planted," Agriculture Minister Sjarifuddin Baharsjah said here
Wednesday after meeting with President Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
He said that rainfall in rice-production areas like West Java
this month has been normal, a situation ensuring that yield would
be good.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the country's acreage of rice fields
will be increased in stages to reach up to 11 million hectares.
</P>
<P>
On the import of rice carried out by the country's logistics
agency, Baharsjah said the move is prudent as it aims to ensure
there is enough rice stock for the people.
</P>
<P>
Last month, Indonesia imported about one million tons of rice
from Thailand, Vietnam, Pakistan and India.  
</P>
