<HEADLINE> Anti-Calamities Headquarters Hold Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 14 (Xinhua) -- A national conference of
directors of drought and flood-control departments in China opened
today in Haikou, the capital of China's island province of Hainan.
</P>
<P>
In a written instruction to the conference, Vice-Premier Jiang
Chunyun, a member of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee Political Bureau, praised the departments for their
contributions in dealing with last year's disasters.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, China had severe droughts and floods but had a good
harvest in spite of them, contributing to economic development and
social stability. Jiang went on to ask departments to do an even
better job in 1998.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to the conference, Water Resources Minister Niu
Maosheng said that 1997 was unusual in water conservation work,
because both the Three Gorges and Xiaolangdi projects, the two
largest dam projects in China, had succeeded in their work.
</P>
<P>
Last year also saw the founding of the Water Conservation Fund
and the adoption of the Law on Flood Control and water
conservation policies, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, he added, local flood and drought-control authorities
need to be prepared for possible major flooding and droughts near
the Yangtze, Yellow, Haihe and Huaihe rivers. 
</P>
