<HEADLINE> Chinese Neuroscientists Set up Research Promotion Organization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Prominent Chinese
Neuroscientists attending a workshop in Hong Kong have agreed to
establish an organization to promote academic exchange and
cooperation between China's inland areas, Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The objectives of the Chinese Brain Research Organization
(CBRO) are to foster collaborative research in basic and clinical
neuroscience, and facilitate exchange of scientific knowledge and
training of high quality scientists, according to the Chinese
University of Hong Kong, which played host to the neuroscience
exchange workshop.
</P>
<P>
A preparatory committee consists of six neuroscientists, with
the inland areas, Hong Kong and Taiwan each having two members.
</P>
<P>
It was agreed that a Chinese Neuroscience Forum will be
organized at the Chinese University in 1999 to celebrate the
inauguration of the organization. 
