<HEADLINE> UK Jobless Rate Continues to Fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 14 (Xinhua) - The British unemployment rate
continued to fall in December to its lowest level in 17
years, according to official figures released here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The number of people out of work and claiming benefits reached
1,411,200. The decline for the month of December numbered 28,700.
The figures have been declining for 22 consecutive months.
</P>
<P>
Other figures released by the Office for National Statistics
showed that average earnings increased by 4.75 percent last year
up to November, a rise of 0.25 percent on the revised rate for
October.
</P>
<P>
Economists here believe the stronger than expected earnings
growth is bound to revive speculation that the Bank of England
will raise interest rates next month.
</P>
<P>
It would be the sixth time Britain has raised interest rates
since Labor came to power last May. 
</P>
