<HEADLINE> China Develops New Amino Acid Fertilizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- A new non-toxic, pollution-free
amino acid fertilizer developed on the island province of Hainan
is now being used in other parts of China.
</P>
<P>
The product was developed by scientists at the Hainan Shenlong
Amino Acid Fertilizer Company. It contains 18 types of amino acid
needed by plants and various trace elements like nitrogen,
phosphorus, and potassium.
</P>
<P>
Because the amino acids can be absorbed by plants without
photosynthesis, the fertilizer is more efficient and can be used
as a substitute for chemical fertilizers that deplete the soil and
affect plant species through overuse, and crop output can increase
15 percent to 20 percent at no greater cost.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture Ministry scientists say the fertilizer could
improve the quality of species, soil, and the ecology, while
increasing output.
</P>
<P>
A fertilizer factory with an annual production capacity of
30,000 ton's has already been set up in Jiangsu Province's
Kunshan, and the Agriculture Ministry has approved a Beijing plant
that can produce 300,000 tons of amino acid fertilizer each year,
and plants in the cities of Guangzhou and Chengdu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
