<HEADLINE> China Expects To Produce 300 Million Tons Of Oil By 2010 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- China will develop six
50-million-ton oil and gasfields by 2010, to produce 300 million
tons of oil and gas equivalent, according to Zhou Yongkang,
president of the China National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC).
</P>
<P>
The six include four inside China and two abroad that will be
built in cooperation with foreign oil companies.
</P>
<P>
The domestic ones are the Songliao Basin in northeastern China,
the Bohai Bay Basin, and Sichuan, the Shaanxi-Gansu-Ningxia area,
and the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region which has an annual gas
capacity of 50 billion cu.m.
</P>
<P>
The two abroad can provide 50 million tons of crude oil and 50
billion cu.m. of natural gas a year.
</P>
<P>
By 2010, the CNPC will be able to produce 200 million tons of
crude oil and 100 billion cu.m. of natural gas. 
