<HEADLINE> Tibetan Leaders Visit Home For Elderly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Officials of the Tibet Autonomous
Region today visited 60 elderly people who live at the Social
Welfare House in the regional capital of Lhasa.
</P>
<P>
The welfare home, which was set up in 1984, is the first to be
built here and has become home for 67 elderly persons and
orphans. They are each given 110 yuan in subsidies from the
government.
</P>
<P>
Last July, Lhasa's Chengguan District began a minimum wage
security system that now covers 2,340 people in 630 families.
</P>
<P>
The regional leaders, including Gyalcan Norbu, chairman of the
regional government, also visited poor families in Lhasa today and
brought welfare residents and poor families butter, tea, beef, and
cash payments. 
</P>
