<HEADLINE> Trade Minister Visits South Pacific Island Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Minister of Foreign Trade and
Economic Cooperation Wu Yi left Beijing today on a visit to Fiji
and Samoa.
</P>
<P>
Wu is leading a Chinese government trade delegation to the
South Pacific Island nations at the invitation of Berenado
Vunibobo, minister of foreign affairs and foreign trade of the
Republic of Fiji, and Tuilaepa Sailele Malielegaoi, deputy prime
