<HEADLINE> Philippine Transportation Secretary Dies of ailment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Philippine Transportation and
Communications Secretary Arturo Enrile died at the age of 57
Wednesday morning in a medical center in Manila, the Presidential
Press Office said.
</P>
<P>
Enrile, who was rushed to hospital Monday due stomach ailment,
died from multiple organ failure as a result of septic shock,
Health Secretary Carmencita Reodica said, citing a report from
Enrile's attending physicians.
</P>
<P>
At his weekly press conference, President Fidel Ramos said he
has designated Josefina Lichauco, a senior official of the
Transportation and Communications Ministry, as acting secretary.
</P>
<P>
Ramos praised Enrile for having "devoted the best years of his
life in the service of the Philippine Government and the Filipino
people."
</P>
<P>
Enrile was appointed by Ramos as transportation secretary in
April 1997 shortly after his retirement as chief of staff of the
Armed Forces. He served as chief of staff from April 1994 to
November 1997.  
</P>
