<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NGO Slams Italy for Detaining Somali Man </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, January 14 (Xinhua) -- A local human rights
organization has condemned the detention of a Somali man by the
Italian police in Rome for his alleged involvement of murder.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Ismail Jumale Human Rights Center (Dr. IHRC) said Tuesday
that the detention of Hashi Omar Hassan is part of a plot by the
Italian government to block the human rights violations committed
by the Italian UNOSOM forces during their operation in Somalia in
1993-94.
</P>
<P>
According to the Italian police, Hassan was among seven Somali
gunmen who allegedly ambushed and killed Elaria Alpi and her
video cameraman working for RAI in March 1994 in North Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The detention of Hassan is contrary to the reason of his
invitation to Italy, said Hassan Shire Sheikh, one of the
co-chairpersons of Dr. IHRC.
</P>
<P>
The center expressed concern that the detainee won't have a
fair trial in Italy and has called on the Italian authorities to
immediately issue, if there are any, charges against Hassan in a
neutral country.
</P>
<P>
"It's unfortunate that the Italian army officers who were
confirmed guilty in violating the basic human rights of some
Somali citizens are still free in Italy," said Shire Sheikh.
</P>
<P>
"The investigative committee has got evidence for cases of
killing, rape and torture in North Mogadishu, Balad and Mahadday
areas of Somalia. However, they failed to bring any of the
accused to the justice," he added.
</P>
<P>
Dr. IHRC said Hassan and his 10 other colleagues including a
woman who were taken from Mogadishu to Italy four days ago are
now in a military camp in the town of Livorno of Italy.
</P>
<P>
The Italian appointed investigative committee is expected to
enquire the 11 Somalis. However, some of them are reported to
have refused to testify the human rights violations unless their
fellow friend, Hassan, is released.
</P>
<P>
The legal advisor of the Somalis in Italy, Hassan Duale, said
they will no longer cooperate with the investigative committee if
the accusations against Hassan are not made clear before the
courts very soon.
</P>
<P>
Hassan told the journalists before his departure from
Mogadishu that he's the only survivor of a group of seventeen
Somalis allegedly drowned in the Indian Ocean by the Italian
armed forces in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"We were tied up at the back together with ropes and sacks of
sand before we were thrown into the sea," said Hassan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
