<HEADLINE> Beijing Snowfall Causes More Traffic Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The snow that has fallen in
Beijing since yesterday afternoon has made the air crisp and
clean, but has increased the number of traffic accidents and
problems.
</P>
<P>
Urban traffic department officials say that by two this
afternoon, they had received about 700 reports of traffic
accidents, most of them minor ones caused by icy conditions, and
no serious accidents or traffic fatalities have been reported.
</P>
<P>
However, six major highways, including those from Beijing to
Tianjin and Beijing to Shijiazhuang, have been closed temporarily.
</P>
<P>
The snow has not delayed any flights at Capital Airport, as
workers rapidly cleared the ice and snow from the runways.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists say the snow will end tomorrow, by which time
there is expected to be an accumulation of five centimeters. The
amount of snowfall in the city proper is now four
centimeters. Temperatures in Beijing tomorrow will be two to three
degrees below zero Centigrade at the most.
</P>
<P>
Li Futing, of the Beijing Meteorology Bureau, says that when
the snow stops, cold and windy weather will set in and will
probably last a week, and snow will remain on most streets for
awhile. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
