<HEADLINE> University to Cooperate With US Firm in Management Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, one of
China's most prestigious universities, and ITT Industries Co., a
leading US-based supplier of automotive parts, have signed a
memorandum of understanding calling for cooperation in the realm
of engineering and business administration education, according to
an ITT representative.
</P>
<P>
The partners initiated the cooperative education project by
sponsoring a seminar to discuss the principles of Edward Deming, a
20th century scholar commonly referred to as the "father of the
quality management."
</P>
<P>
The seminar attracted more than 50 experts from the automotive
and manufacturing industries in China and the United States, as
well as teachers and students from Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
"ITT is committed to China's industrial growth and is
implementing the cooperative program with Qinghua in order to
sponsor advanced technical seminars to support engineering and
management education. The company will also help foster continued
economic growth and prosperity for the country and its joint
venture partners," according to Roy Sheldon, chairman and general
manager of ITT Industries China.
</P>
<P>
ITT Industries also signed a cooperative agreement with
Shanghai's Jiaotong University to increase academic exchanges in
the fields of engineering and management education.
</P>
<P>
ITT Industries has established five joint ventures in Shanghai,
Shenyang, Nanjing and Zhenjiang to produce automobile and
telecommunications components and wastewater treatment equipment.
</P>
</TEXT>
