<HEADLINE> Power Restored to Quake-Stricken Villages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Electric Power supply has
been restored to all villages in Shangyi and Zhangbei counties,
Zhangjiakou Prefecture, in north China's Hebei Province, an area
devastated by a strong earthquake on January 10.
</P>
<P>
The low-voltage power network in the area was heavily damaged,
with broken power line and poles, collapsed control centers, and
damaged transformers.
</P>
<P>
The Zhangjiakou Power Company dispatched 200 experts to repair
the network. Electric Power supply was restored to shelters and
tents in all villages by 10:00 a.m. today.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which measured 6.2 on the Richter Scale, hit the
area at 11:50 (Beijing Time) last Saturday. The devastating quake
killed 49 people, injured more than 2,000 local residents and
damaged over 150,000 houses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
