<HEADLINE> Portuguese Grand Prix Cancelled from Calendar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Portuguese Grand Prix,
scheduled on October 11, was dropped from the 1998 Formula One
world championship calendar on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A statement from motor racing's ruling body FIA said requested
safety work would not be completed within a specified time limit.
</P>
<P>
The future of the Belgian Grand Prix, which will only take
place if there are guarantees that the country's tobacco
advertising ban will not affect the race, still remains in doubt.
</P>
<P>
FIA has given the organisers until February 15 to resolve the
problem.
</P>
<P>
The country to replace Portugal will be announced soon. South
Africa and China are the candidates.  
