<HEADLINE> Four Chinese Swimmers Tested Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Four Chinese swimmers have tested
positive for banned drugs in out-of-competition doping tests,
world swimming ruling body the International Swimming Federation
(FINA) announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
FINA said in a press release that Chinese women swimmers Wang
Luna, Cai Huijue and Zhang Yi and men swimmer Wang Wei tested
positive for the banned substance Triamterene (diuretic).
</P>
<P>
