<HEADLINE> MTRC (Amendment) Bill 1997 Adopted by HK Legislature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Provisional
Legislative Council approved the Mass Transit Railway Corporation
(Amendment) Bill 1997 after the third reading here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the amended Ordinance, the Secretary for Transport and
the
MTRC will have the power to make regulation and by-law governing
the operation and management, in particular traffic control and
the operation of public transport and of transport interchanges of
the Airport Railway.
</P>
<P>
The Airport Railway consists of two lines: Airport Express Line
running between Central on the Hong Kong Island and the new
airport with stops at four stations of Hong Kong, Kowloon, Tsing
Yi and the airport; and the Tung Chung Line, a conventional mass
transit service with stops at six stations of Hong Kong, Kowloon,
Olympic, Lai King, Tsing Yi and Tung Chung.
</P>
<P>
MTRC is responsible for the design, construction, completion,
management and maintenance of transport interchanges at the Hong
Kong, Kowloon and Tsing Yi stations. To enable the MTRC to fulfill
this responsibility, regulation and by-law governing the relevant
transport interchanges needs to be made.
</P>
<P>
During Wednesday's Plenary Session, the provisional legislators
also had second reading of the Housing (Amendment) Bill 1998 and
the Immigration (Amendment) Bill 1998.
</P>
<P>
Government officials answered dozens of questions in a written
or oral way on environment protection and on how to maintain Hong
Kong's status as an international shipping center and how to
prevent the occurrence of domestic violence.  
</P>
</TEXT>
