<HEADLINE> HK-Shenzhen Express Train Services to Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Beginning from the end of
this month, people can travel between Hong Kong and Shenzhen by
taking a non-stop express train, according to Kowloon-Canton
Railway Corporation (KCRC) officials.
</P>
<P>
KCRC has decided to start a temporary express service between
Hunghom, Kowloon, and Lowu which separates Hong Kong and Shenzhen
in Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The new non-stop train service was introduced because the
Kowloon-Canton Through Train service to Guangzhou has been delayed
and will not be operational until the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Passengers can complete immigration procedures at Hungkom and
use a special exit at Lowu to enter Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
A newly-introduced model of train will double the passenger
seating capacity to 1,200 and shorten the 110-minute trip to
Guangzhou by 15 minutes when traveling at a speed of 160
kilometers an hour, KCRC officials said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
