<HEADLINE> HK, Canada Sign Environmental Cooperation Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong and Canada
Wednesday signed a new agreement to further enhance cooperation in
the field of environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The memorandum of understanding was signed here by Bowen Leung,
secretary for planning, environment and lands of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR), and Christine Stewart,
Canada's minister of environment.
</P>
<P>
The accord, first signed in 1992, will cover a period of five
years.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Hong Kong and Canada will provide each
other with information on environmental issues and on significant
environmental research, monitoring, socioeconomic impact and
regulatory and policy elements of their respective programs.
</P>
<P>
The document has identified a number of areas as priority
issues for further cooperation, including sustainable development,
pollution prevention, waste reduction, clean technology and
waste-to-energy incineration.
</P>
<P>
"In these and many other areas, we hope to improve our
understanding of the considerations made by Canada, the options
examined and the solutions selected," Leung said, adding that Hong
Kong hopes to offer its Canadian counterparts something useful in
return.  
</P>
</TEXT>
