<HEADLINE> Five Chinese Provinces Speeding Up Industrialization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Rapid industrialization in
Hubei, Hunan and Henan proinces in central China and Anhui and
Jiangxi provinces in east China have sped up in the past 17 years.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, the five
provinces' combined industrial output now accounts for 42 percent
of their GDP.
</P>
<P>
In 1980, their industrial output accounted for 40 percent of
their total GDP.
</P>
<P>
Experts say these provinces can be built into bases for
agricultural produce, raw materials and machine building in the
next 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Some economists are said to be making an overall plan for
speeding up industrialization in these provinces. 
</P>
