<HEADLINE> Macao Increases Police Patrol in Streets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Macao police have increased
patrol in the downtown area in a bid to fight against rising
crimes before the Chinese Lunar New Year.
</P>
<P>
Local Chinese radio broadcast said on Wednesday that the number
of policemen on patrol has gone up by about 40 percent over normal
times and most of them are deployed in places where gold shops and
banks are located.
</P>
<P>
Crime is said to usually rise before the Spring Festival, which
 falls on January 28 this year. A number of gold shop robberies
have already occurred over the past 20 days.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Security Police Department said there will
be about 140 policemen on patrol at the same time now, compared
with the usual 100.
</P>
<P>
The increased presence of police patrol will last until
mid-February, when the holidays of the Spring Festival wrap up.
</P>
