<HEADLINE> Swimmer Yuan Banned for 4 Years, Her Coach 15 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese swimmer Yuan Yuan and her
coach Zhou Zhewen, both held responsible for bringing a banned
drug into Australia, have received lengthy suspensions from the
world swimming ruling body the International Swimming Federation
(FINA).
</P>
<P>
FINA announced here on Wednesday that Yuan had been banned for
four years from any international and national competition and
Zhou for 15 years.
</P>
<P>
The bans started on January 8, the day the Sydney Customs found
banned drug growth hormone in Yuan's handbag during the two's
stopover at Sydney.
</P>
<P>
Zhou told a FINA doping panel on January 10 that he asked Yuan
to carry the "substance", which was to be delivered to a friend in
Australia. The coach said that neither he or Yuan knew the
substance was a banned drug.
</P>
<P>
Yuan and Zhou, who both were suspended from the world
championships by the Chinese delegation late January 8, had
arrived in Beijing last night. 
</P>
