<HEADLINE> Uganda's Tea Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's tea production this
year is expected to exceed earlier projection of 20 million
kilograms, the Uganda Tea Authority said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda produced 18.3 million kilograms of tea by the end of
November, 1997, an 17 percent increase compared with 15.7 million
kilograms in the same period in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Peter Rolland, General Manager of Rwenzori Highland Tea
Company, said the rainy weather has spurred the growth of tea.
</P>
<P>
The weather affected only transport and labour needed in the
collection of the crop, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said his company is expected to produce 7,200 tons of tea,
an 20 percent increase as against last year's 6,000 tons. Last
year, his firm produced 15 percent of the total production in
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Uganda produced 17,148 tons of tea in 1996, nearly three times
more than the 6,740 tons in 1990. The export of 14,611 tons
brought an income of nearly 15 million dollars in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
