<HEADLINE> NATO Chief to Be on Promise-Keeping Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 14 (Xinhua) -- NATO Secretary General Javier
Solana is expected to visit in the coming weeks several countries
interested in joining the western military alliance.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the NATO headquarters said Wednesday that Solana
intends, during his trip to the three accession candidates of
Poland, Hungary and the Czech Republic, to drop by Slovenia and
Slovakia in a gesture that NATO remains open to those who aspire
to join it.
</P>
<P>
Solana will kick off his promise-keeping trip next week.
</P>
