<HEADLINE> French Institution Pledges Financial Aid to SADC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The French overseas
financing institution, Caisse Francaise de
Developpement-Proparco, today pledged 46.8 million U.S. dollars
to finance new investment and facilities for a number of projects
in the Southern African Development Community region.
</P>
<P>
South African Press Association quoted the institution as
reporting that the French-aided projects are based in Namibia,
Mozambique, Zambia and Tanzania. The projects include a 800,000
U.S. Dollar subsidy for an investment feasibility study in
Nambia, a six million dollar subsidy for the rehabilitation of
Mozambique's Chokwe Agricultural Irrigation Scheme, a 25.6
million dollar package to finance the Mozambican Aluminium
Smelter Project in Maputo, a 10.9 million dollar facility for the
rehabilitation of the Kafue Gorge Power Station in Zambia, and a
3.5 million dollar subsidy to Tanesco, the Tanzanian electricity
utility.
</P>
<P>
CFD-Procarco said the financial package shows its continued
belief in the success of Southern Africa's regional development.
</P>
</TEXT>
