<HEADLINE> Over 250,000 People in Mozambican Province Need </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 14 (Xinhua) -- About 250,000 people in
Mutarara county of the westnorthern province of Tete have been
suffering from grain shortage since autumn last year, local
newspaper Noticias reported today.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that farmers in the county failed to get any
harvest last autumn after heavy rains hit the county. Some
non-governmental organizations there are trying to pool some food
for the hunger-stricken farmers.
</P>
<P>
Silvano Langa, Director of the Department of Natural Disaster
Prevention said that the organization is taking measures to cut
down the influence of El Nino effect.
</P>
<P>
Langa said that 1.1 million people of the country's total
population of 15 million need food aid, and only 0.17 million
people could benefit from current humanitarian aid.
</P>
<P>
The World Food Program and the Mozambican government have sent
delegations to inspect southern provinces where food aid is
badly needed. 
</P>
