<HEADLINE> Allegations of Thai Guerrillas Being Trained in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The umbrella organization
for six Muslim liberation fronts in Thailand has categorically
denied the allegations by Thai authorities that their guerrillas
are being trained in Malaysia, according to the Malaysian national
news agency Bernama Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The denial was made by the Patani Malay Consultative Congress
known as MPRMP based in Hamburg, Germany, in letter sent to
Bernama which was received here Wednesday, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
"We are responsible for all activities of our guerrillas in the
Malay provinces of southern Thailand," the letter signed by
Mohamad Haris Hadafi, Press Secretary of the MPRMP President, was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
MPRMP is said to be the umbrella organization for the Patani
Islamic Liberation Front, National Revolutionary Front, National
Revolutionary Front-Congress, Patani Mujahidin Movement, Patani
Ulama Movement and Patani United Liberation Organization (PULO).
</P>
<P>
There were reported allegations from the Thai authorities
recently that Malaysia was a training ground for PULO rebels.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Defense Minister Syed Hamid Albar and Deputy
Inspector-General of Police Norian Mai both have denies the
charge.
</P>
<P>
However, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said
Tuesday after meeting Thai Deputy Foreign Minister Sukhumbhand
Paribatra that he was open to discussing the allegations with his
Thai counterpart Surin Pitsuwan at their meeting expected to be
held here next month when Surin will pay his first official visit
to Malaysia since his appointment as foreign minister in last
November.
</P>
<P>
If Thailand has any information or evidence of this matter,
then it will be discussed by Surin and myself during Surin's
visit, Abdullah said.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said Malaysia's policy was not to interfere with the
internal affairs of another country and likewise it did not want
to be a base for such groups from other countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
