<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major Uganda-Kenya Road Blocked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The main road linking Uganda
and Kenya via Malaba border post has been blocked due to the
collapse of a bridge there, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
More than 400 heavily-loaded trucks to Kampala, southern
Sudan, Rwanda and Democratic Congo have been stranded, the report
added.
</P>
<P>
Another way from Kenya to Uganda is via Busia border post. But
Kenyan officials on the border post said they have received
instruction from the Kenya Revenue Authority in Nairobi not to
allow "sensitive" cargo back to reroute the vehicles via Busia.
</P>
<P>
The alternative for the stranded cargo is to transport from
Port Kisumu in Kenya to Port Bell in Uganda through Lake
Victoria.
</P>
<P>
Oofficials of the Malaba border post has appealed to the
Ugandan Ministry of Works, Transport and Communications to
dispatch engineers to reopen the road, assess the damage and
repair the bridge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
