<HEADLINE> Russia, Turkmenistan Sign Agreement on Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Russia and Turkmenistan signed
an agreement on avoiding dual taxation Wednesday, according to the
Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
The accord was reached during the second round of talks by
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and Turkmen President
Saparmurad Niyazov in Ashgabat, capital of Turkmenistan.
</P>
<P>
The Interfax said that the talks focused on a wide range of
issues including bilateral economic contacts, cooperation in the
production and transportation of natural gas and the legal status
of the Caspian Sea.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin had his first round of talks with the Turkmen
president upon his arrival in Ashgabat on Tuesday. The talks was
focused on Turkmenistan's gas transportation to CIS markets and
Europe.
</P>
<P>
The Russian premier is expected to fly to Dushanbe for talks
with Tajik President Emomali Rakhmonov Wednesday afternoon.
During the visit, the two sides are expected to sign a package of
bilateral agreements, the Interfax said. 
</P>
