<HEADLINE> Chen Yan Wins Women's 400m Freestyle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PERTH, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese top swimmer Chen Yan came
from behind to win the women's 400m freestyle final at the world
swimming championships here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Chen, 400m individual medley world champion of
two days, surged ahead to touch the pad first at 350 meters and
kept the lead to clock four minutes 6.72 seconds.
</P>
<P>
American Brooke Bennet, who conceded the lead to Chen at the
last turn, picked the silver medal in 4:07.07.
</P>
<P>
European champion Dagmar Hase of Germany touched the pad in
4:08.82 for the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Olympic champion Claudia Poll of Costa Rica, ranked No.2 last
year, finished last eighth in 4:12.08. 
