<HEADLINE> Pak PM to Attend Tripartite Summit in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister
Nawaz Sharif will leave here Thursday morning for Dhaka to attend
a trilateral economic summit, which will also be attended by the
prime ministers of India and Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The summit will help increase economic cooperation among the
three countries and in the region, the Associated Press of
Pakistan quoted official sources as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The three prime ministers will discuss various aspects on
cooperation in the fields of infrastructure, trade and industry,
the sources said.
</P>
<P>
After attending the one-day summit, Sharif will pay a two-day
visit to Bangladesh starting from Friday, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
