<HEADLINE> Seminar Marks 100th anniversary of Zhou Enlai's Birth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Nankai University, alma mater
of the late Chinese Premier Zhou Enlai, held a seminar today in
Beijing with the Western Returned Scholars Association to mark the
100th anniversary of the birth of the Chinese leader.
</P>
<P>
Zhou began his studies at Nankai University in 1919, and was
among the first group of students at the school. He is regarded as
the most outstanding alumnus of the university.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jieping, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee and president of the Western Returned Scholars
Association, discussed Zhou's instructions in today's seminar when
recalling his days as a medical expert working with the Chinese
leader.
</P>
<P>
Even when Zhou suffered serious illness and received medical
treatment, he still worked for state affairs, Wu said. He called
on the returned students from overseas to follow Zhou's spirit of
dedication as well as his noble personality.
</P>
<P>
Kong Fanfeng, vice-president of Nankai University, told
participants about recent discoveries by the university's Zhou
Enlai Research Center, especially the leadership he demonstrated
among students studying overseas when Zhou was studying in Europe.
</P>
</TEXT>
