<HEADLINE> Qingdao Opens Shipping Route to Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Qingdao in east China's
Shandong Province opened a new international shipping route to the
Japanese city of Shimonoseki on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The city's first international shipping route continues to
offer regularly scheduled services to Inchon in the Republic of
Korea. The new route, which will be managed by a Shimonoseki-based
steamer company, was jointly established by Shandong Province and
three Japanese companies.
</P>
<P>
The regularly scheduled ship will arrive in Qingdao at 07:30 on
Monday and depart for Shimonoseki at 16:00 on Thursday. It will
dock in Shimonoseki at 09:30 on Saturday and depart for Qingdao at
16:00 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 10,000-dwt vessel used on the route can carry 336
passengers and 148 standardized containers.
</P>
<P>
Since 1980, a Japanese tour ship has made irregular voyages on
the route. 
</P>
