<HEADLINE> Microsoft Establishes Technical Support Center in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Microsoft Corp. opened a
technical support center Tuesday in China's leading industrial
city of Shanghai with nearly 10 million U.S. dollars of investment.
</P>
<P>
Steve Ballmer, the company's deputy chief executive officer,
said the Microsoft Greater China Regional Support Center, is the
corporation's fifth technical support center.
</P>
<P>
The other four were established in the United States, Japan,
Australia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Ballmer said the Shanghai-based center provides telephone, fax
and electronic mail consultations and on-the-spot service for
Microsoft's subscribers in China.
</P>
<P>
He added that the new center has been equipped with advanced
digital telephones, computer systems and dozens of technicians.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft chose to establish its technical support center in
Shanghai because it is China's top economic center with many
institutions of higher education and software development centers.
</P>
<P>
Ballmer said the opening of the center will promote the spread
of Microsoft's master software in China as well as the development
of the country's software industry.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. company has 500 sales agents and 150 technical
training centers in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
