<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sharp Increase in Foreign Trade in South China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 14 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong
Province saw its foreign trade increase dramatically last year.
</P>
<P>
The province's import-export volume reached 115.7 billion US
dollars at the end of last November, up 19.9 percent from the same
period of 1996, according to official statistics. Exports were
67.2 billion dollars, up 27.1 percent, and imports were 48.5
billion dollars, up 11.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's foreign-funded enterprises were still the leading
force in its foreign trade. Their trade volume stood at 61.6
billion dollars in the 11-month period, or 53.3 percent
of the total.
</P>
<P>
Exports and imports of state-owned enterprises, which had
dropped considerably in 1996, were 50 billion dollars in the
period, up 25.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that trade volume in the processing
industry was 84.3 billion dollars by November, or 72.9
percent of the province's total. Most products for the overseas
market were high-tech products that are capital- and
technology-intensive.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
