<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Subway to Be Completed in Mid-1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Track-laying for the first
subway line in the capital of south China's Guangdong Province
will be completed in July this year.
</P>
<P>
The subway will be put into trial operation at the end of the
year, according to Wang Wenbin, deputy manager of the Guangzhou
Subway Corporation.
</P>
<P>
A 5.4-km section of the line went on trial operation last
June and construction of its 11 stations have been going on
smoothly, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the 18.5-km-long subway, with a total
investment of 13.8 billion yuan, started in December in 1993.
</P>
<P>
He also disclosed that construction of the city's second subway
line is expected to begin later this year. The 21.3-km line, half
of which will be light rail, will cost about 10 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
