<HEADLINE> Chinese Arbitration Committee Accepts 723 Cases in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese International
Economic and Trade Arbitration Committee (CIETAC) accepted 723
cases last year, leading the profession for a fifth consecutive
year, today's International Business Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
CIETAC accepted 486 cases in 1993, becoming the No.1 arbitrator
for the first time, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In last year's cases, the litigants came from 45 countries and
regions including the United States, Japan, Germany, Britain,
France and Hong Kong. The amount of money involved increased
notably.
</P>
<P>
There were 23 cases in which both litigants were foreign
businesses. 
</P>
