<HEADLINE> Schools in Quake-Hit Areas to Reopen on Schedule </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- An official from quake-stricken
areas in Hebei Province says the provincial education department
will allocate sufficient funding to ensure that the schools in
affected areas can reopen as scheduled next term.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,326 school houses in Zhangbei and Shangyi counties were
destroyed during the devastating January 10 earthquake which
measured 6.2 on the Richter Scale, according to the local
education department. Fortunately, schools in both counties were
on winter vacation at the time, with the new term scheduled to
begin on March 6.
</P>
<P>
Yang Qian, deputy-governor of Hebei Province, said that
priority will be placed on ensuring that local farmers have
adequate food and housing, as well as on rebuilding schools.
</P>
<P>
According to the Hebei Education Commission, teachers in
seriously affected areas have been granted allowances of 300 yuan
each. In addition, a Hong Kong education foundation founded by
famous film producer Run Run Shaw, has pledged to rebuild two Hope
Project schools in the area.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that construction work will begin in May due to
prevailing adverse weather conditions. Therefore, numerous classes
will be held in tents, and a number of structurally sound houses
will be transformed into classrooms.
</P>
<P>
Officials note that many of an additional 3,100 tents which
will be transported to the earthquake-stricken area will be used
as classrooms.  
</P>
</TEXT>
