<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in Pakistan Up by 7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Foreign direct investment in
Pakistan registered a 7-percent increase in the first five months
of the current fiscal year over a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Latest figures by the Board of Investment show that foreign
direct investment from July to November 1997 stood at 285 million
U.S. dollars, 7 percent higher than the corresponding period last
year.
</P>
<P>
The power sector ranked top by attracting 114.6 million of the
total 285 million dollar investment during the period.
</P>
<P>
It was followed by the chemical, farming and fertilizer
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Other industries which received foreign direct investment
included tourism, electrical machinery, food, beverages, tobacco
and transport equipment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
