<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wellington, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
rose Wednesday following a strong close on Wall Street overnight
and rebounds on Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 22 points higher at 2236 with a turnover
of 53 million dollars (30 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares led the rise, leaping by 15 cents to 790 cents
and accounting for half of the turnover. Also higher were Carter
Holt Harvey, gaining 5 cents to 270 cents; Fletcher Energy 25
cents to 605 cents; and Lion Nathan 10 cents to 417 cents.
</P>
<P>
However, Air New Zealand eased 3 cents to 215 cents while
Brierley Investment remained unchanged at 110 cents.
</P>
<P>
Overall, there were 48 rises and 47 falls.  
</P>
</TEXT>
