<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi to Boost Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Shaanxi Province, home of the
"Terra Cotta Warriors," plans to attract 600,000 overseas visitors
and make 250 million U.S. dollars from international tourism in
1998.
</P>
<P>
The northwest Chinese province also expects 25 million domestic
tourists to generate 7.4 billion yuan (891.56 million
U.S. dollars) this year.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 the province, one of the most popular tourist
destinations in China, received a record 540,000 overseas tourists
and more than 25 million domestic visitors, an increase of 8
percent and 9 percent over 1996, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The province has designated tourism as one of the pace-setting
sectors to make breakthroughs this year.
</P>
<P>
Li Jianguo, provincial head of the Communist Party of China,
recently called for improving the management and marketing of
tourism.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Andong, governor of Shaanxi Province, called for more and
improved tourist facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
