<DOCNO> XIE19980114.0266 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Official Urges U.S. to Open Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Thai Deputy Foreign Minister
Sukhumbhand Paribatra has urged the United States to help Thailand
by opening its market.
</P>
<P>
Another thing that the United States can do is improve
conditions for investment in Thailand, Sukhumbhand was quoted by
the Bangkok Post Wednesday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Thailand would not ask the United States for financial support
as the Clinton administration is known to be under pressure from
the congress, the paper also quoted government sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Sukhumbhand was commenting on a brief visit to Thailand by U.S.
Deputy Treasury Secretary Lawrence Summers, who is scheduled to
call on Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Reports say it is up to Summers to come up with a proposal for
the Clinton administration to help speed up the recovery of Asia's
troubled economies.
</P>
<P>
Since Thailand began suffering financial turmoil last year, it
has got no financial assistance from the U.S. government except
that through the International Monetary Fund (IMF), which arranged
a 17.2 billion U.S. dollar bailout program for the country.
</P>
<P>
Some Thai sources suggested that the United States increase
contributions to the IMF, whose funds are fast depleting, or
encourage international organizations such as the World Bank to
beef up assistance to affected countries in terms of social safety
net programs or technical cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They also expect the U.S. government to convince the G-7 Group
of Western industrialized countries to help Asian countries find
ways out of the economic turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sukhumbhand revealed on Tuesday that the Philippines
has proposed to hold a special meeting on the region's economic
crisis, to be attended by ministers of finance, commerce and
foreign affairs of five ASEAN members -- Indonesia, Malaysia, the
Philippines, Singapore and Thailand.  
</P>
</TEXT>
