<HEADLINE> State-Owned Enterprises Get Head Start in Recruiting Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 14 (Xinhua) -- State-owned enterprises in
north China's port city of Tianjin have begun recruiting qualified
college graduates nearly half a year before the end of school.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the city's Hebei District,
government bodies and state-owned enterprises are seeking 150
graduates in 20 majors including law and business administration.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Tianjin human resources department
attributed this year's early recruitment to reforms in state-owned
enterprises. Some enterprises have signed contracts with
universities to train professionals.
</P>
<P>
Traditionally, recruitment would not start until March or
April. Most enterprises recruiting employees through job markets
are foreign-funded or privately owned. State-owned enterprises
that recruit employees in job markets constitute less than 10
percent of the total.  
</P>
</TEXT>
