<HEADLINE> Fuzhou to Woo More Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou, capital of east China's
Fujian Province, has provided 179 key projects this year for
foreign investors' consideration.
</P>
<P>
The investment in these projects is expected to reach 12.3
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
These projects cover a wide range of sectors: 20 in
infrastructure and basic industries involving an investment of 9.6
billion U.S. dollars; 49 in agriculture; 38 in upgrading state
firms; and 72 in the service sector.
</P>
<P>
The city, hometown for many overseas Chinese, has developed
rapidly as a result of exchanges with the outside world.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 the city approved 430 foreign-funded projects, up 5
percent over 1996, and spent 1.15 billion U.S. dollars in foreign
funds, up 2.8 percent over last year. 
