<HEADLINE> Russian Premier Talks Gas Trade in Turkmenistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin Tuesday discussed gas trade with Turkmenistan's
president, Saparmurat Niyazov, in Ashgabat, the Turkmenistan
capital.
</P>
<P>
In their first round of talks, they discussed bilateral
cooperation on fuel and energy, in particular the thorny issue of
Turkmenistan's natural gas exports to the Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS) and the Baltic, said Itar-Tass news
agency.
</P>
<P>
The positive influence of the Soviet Union's collapse, which
was reflected in Russia-Turkmenistan relations, should be cleared
up as soon as possible, said Chernomyrdin.
</P>
<P>
The premier also expressed satisfaction in the increasing trade
volume between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Niyazov stressed on his part the importance of Chernomyrdin's
visit to his country, saying it marked the beginning of a new
stage in the two countries' economic and political cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Governmental delegations of the two sides also held talks in
Ashgabat Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides reportedly decided that an agreement on avoiding
double-taxation between the two countries should be signed after
Chernomyrdin and Niyazov hold a second round of talks on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin and his high-level delegation arrived at Ashgabat
Tuesday for a working visit to this central Asian nation. 
