<HEADLINE> Canadian Company to Grant Mexican Banks Credits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A Canadian company is to
provide more than 127 million U.S. dollars in credit to two Mexican
banks.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached during the current visit by a Canadian
trade mission, the Team Canada, to Mexico starting Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's state-run National Foreign Commerce Bank said that
it has obtained from Canada's Export Development Corp. a credit of
125 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The credit will mainly go to finance capital assets and service
imports from Canada.
</P>
<P>
Another 2.44 million dollars worth of credit was granted to the
National Rural Credit Bank to finance cattle breeders and local
institutions of credits.
</P>
<P>
The 13-day mission, headed by Canadian Governor-General Romeo
LeBlanc to visit Mexico, Brazil, Argentina and Chile, involves
more than 500 politicians, civil servants and business
executives. 
