<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bulgarian Thracian Antiques Put on Show in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 pieces of Bulgarian
antiques will be exhibited in the United States for 20 months, the
Bulgarian Telegraph Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
An official of the Cultural Ministry told the press Tuesday
that the exhibition "Thracian Treasures -- Antiques from Bulgaria"
will be held first at St. Louis Art Museum, starting February 6.
</P>
<P>
They will be on display later in another six museums, the
official said.
</P>
<P>
The treasures are part of the collections from 19 Bulgarian
museums that introduced the ancient Thracian culture.
</P>
<P>
The Thracian people, who settled down here around 700 BC, were
the earliest inhabitants known in Bulgaria. They were assimilated
by the Slavs who massed into this land later.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of ancient Thracian graves were unearthed in recent
centuries, in which many antiques were discovered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980114.0296 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
