strengthened in the advances made in building up a socialist market
economic structure and in opening wider to the world.
</P>
<P>
China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- A new round of economic growth is expected to be sparked by
developments in the residential housing sector, which is drawing
more attention from the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese government will oppose any official contact
between Taiwan and a country which has diplomatic ties with China.
</P>
<P>
China's stand was reiterated yesterday by Foreign Ministry
spokesman Shen Guofang during a routine news briefing in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- A cold front will pass through the earthquake-hit area
northwest of Hebei Province Sunday, adding difficulty to the
relief work in the quake-hit region.
</P>
<P>
The cold front, moving in from Northeast China, is getting
stronger. A dramatic drop in temperature and northwest wind of
force 6 will sweep through the area. 
</P>
