<HEADLINE> Hebei Boosts Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The investment environment
in north China's Hebei Province has been greatly improved owning
to the construction of infrastructures in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Its investment in fixed assets grew at an annual rate of 37.3
percent in the past five years. A total of 173 key projects have
been built.
</P>
<P>
The province has invested 15 billion yuan in building new or
repairing existing roads with a total length of 21,000 km in the
past five years.
</P>
<P>
This brought the total mileage of operational roads in Hebei to
54,000 km, a provincial communication official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Four expressways have opened to traffic. Over 93 percent of the
villages have access to the national or provincial highway
networks.
</P>
<P>
The telephone switch boards in Hebei have six million lines,
7.8 times the 1992 figure. This made it possible for every five
urban residents to share one telephone.
</P>
<P>
New power plants have been built in Qinhuangdao, Xibaipo and
Hengshui cities with an aggregated newly added generating capacity
of 4.26 million kw. 
</P>
