<HEADLINE> Thailand's BOI to Trim Overseas Offices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Board of Investment (BOI)
of Thailand will close or downsize its overseas bureaus to cut
spending in line with the government's austerity policy, local
press reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The BOI's Sydney office will be closed and the staff recalled,
while its Frankfurt office, which has been downsized through
laying off local staff, will also be shut down.
</P>
<P>
The Thai staff in Frankfurt will be moved to the Paris office,
which will now be responsible for all European Union countries.
</P>
<P>
The Osaka office will also be closed and its staff will be
moved to the Thai consulate there, which receives many
business-related inquiries.
</P>
<P>
The number of staff at the other offices in Tokyo and in the
United States will also be cut.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Industry Ministry will close its office of
Industrial Affairs in Britain but those in the United States,
Australia and Japan will remain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
