<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nanjing Customs Creates New High in Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The Nanjing customs registered
a record high tax revenue of five billion yuan (about 600 million
U.S. dollars) last year.
</P>
<P>
The customs collected an additional tax of 97.37 million yuan
(about 11.7 million dollars) by improving the accuracy of
commodity classification and price check of the imported goods,
the International Business Daily has reported.
</P>
<P>
The customs strengthened the normal collection of tax
according to law and joined efforts with relevant departments
concerned to combat tax evasion. In 1997, it collected a total
supplementary tax of 650 million yuan (about 78 million dollars)
through checking those imported material for processing at home.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the customs in the neighboring port
city of Zhenjiang started to use an automatic system in customs
declaration, the first of its kind in the country.
</P>
<P>
The use of this computerized system indicates the introduction
of no-paper-work in the customs service. The time of each
declaration has been reduced from the original 90 minutes to six
minutes and the goods' passing time from the original two hours to
20 minutes, thus greatly reducing the cost of customers.
</P>
<P>
The city's maritime transport started to pilot the computerized
system as of last July.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
