<HEADLINE> Hebei Improves Textile Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province, a leading
textile manufacturer in north China, will raise the efficiency of
its textile industry by readjusting industrial structure this year.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Hebei has 20-odd large cotton mills built in the
1950s or 1960s with 3.4 million spindles, 819,000 of which are
obsolete.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has decided to eliminate 690,000
obsolete cotton spindles this year. The move will lead to the
merger or close-down of a dozen cotton mills and the laid-off of
an estimated 40,000 workers, said a local textile official.
</P>
<P>
Another 129,000 spindles will be eliminated next year.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 80 percent of the spindles to be abandoned belong to 26
large enterprise groups located in six textile centers.
</P>
<P>
The reduction of spindles will help these enterprise groups to
optimize their assets and upgrade technology and equipment, the
official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
