<HEADLINE> Large Plots of Poppy Plantations Destroyed in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 14 (Xinhua) -- A total of 10,352 hectares of
illicit poppy plantations were destroyed by the local authorities
in Myanmar's Shan state during the last two months, the official
New Light of Myanmar newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The plantations, which were secretly grown in a dozen townships
in the northern, southern and eastern parts of Shan state, were
destroyed by the local Myanmar Defense Services Intelligence units
and the police force between November 6 last year and January 5
this year.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, a total of 16,855 hectares of
poppy plantations, most of which in Shan state, were destroyed in
the whole country during the period between 1988 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
The statistics also show that in 1997, the authorities
uncovered and destroyed 33 opium refineries in Shan state and
confiscated a total of 9,800 kilograms of narcotic drugs in the
whole country, including heroin, opium and stimulant tablets.
</P>
</TEXT>
