<HEADLINE> State Key Railway Project Under Construction in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 14 (Xinhua) -- Track laying on a key state
railway line has been basicly completed in central China's Hunan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The regional railway running from Shimeng to Changsha, capital
of the province, has a total length of 264 km. It has been
co-invested by the Ministry of Railways who shares two thirds of
the stake and the provincial People's Government, with total
investment estimated at 3.3 billion yuan (397 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
After completion, the railway will become part of the state
Category-A railway network, which is expected to greatly ease the
strain on the Beijing-Kowloon Railway, China's north-south artery
line and facilitate coal transportation from the northern part of
China to the south.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the railway, which used modern technology,
started in 1994. It runs through resource-rich areas in the
province. 
