<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican Foreign Minister
Fernando Naranjo has arrived on Belgium in his European tour to
explain the situation in the Costa Rican banana industry,
according to a statement from the Foreign Ministry on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Naranjo began a tour through four European countries on Monday,
accompanied by representatives of the banana sector.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Minister, on Monday and Tuesday, met European
banana importers and representatives of protesting groups who have
criticized working conditions at plantations in Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
His tour is part of a government effort to counteract a
campaign fostered by Costa Rican and European organizations
against alleged violations to workers` rights, and to
environmental norms, by banana companies in Costa Rica.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rican authorities and companies have claimed that working
conditions in local plantations are much better than those in
other banana-producing countries.
</P>
<P>
They also assert that banana companies have adopted standards
for environmental conservation.
</P>
<P>
Bananas are the top export of Costa Rica and the European
campaign has caused concern in the private sector and in the
government.
</P>
<P>
Before his European tour, Naranjo said that the campaign might
not only endanger exports but also might affect other products.
</P>
<P>
Naranjo met in London on Monday with British deputies of Foreign
and Agriculture Ministers. Naranjo was also expected to visit
Germany and Norway, the statement said. 
</P>
