<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Diversifies Sources of Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The sources of investment in
fixed assets in this largest economic center of China have
diversified over the last 15 years while the total volume keeps
expanding fast.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Shanghai's investment in fixed
assets totaled 731.4 billion yuan in the last one and half
decades, up by an average of 24.7 percent each year. The yearly
value of investment surged from 7.1 billion yuan in 1982 to 195.2
billion yuan last year.
</P>
<P>
Over the years the state-owned sector was predominant, with
fixed-asset investment by state-owned units adding up to 517.5
billion yuan, or 70.8 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Investment by collective units accounted for 14 percent, that
by private investors 2.5 percent and that by overseas investors
9.7 percent, with the remaining 2.9 percent by other investors.
</P>
<P>
The proportion of investment by different types of investors
underwent marked change in Shanghai between 1993 and 1996, with
the share of investment in fixed assets by state-owned units down
from 69.1 to 62.1 percent. The portion by collective units also
dropped, from 18.9 to 12.2 percent, while that by overseas
investors roared from 9.4 to 17.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also indicate that investment with funds
directly raised by enterprises has continued to grow at a rising
momentum over the last three years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
