<P>
The coastguards from the two countries had traced the ship
named "Demo", and apprehended the 150-ton vessel in Albanian
waters.
</P>
<P>
The vessel, loaded with boxes of well-known foreign cigarettes
taken aboard in a Greek port, was sent under escort to the
Albanian port of Durres.
</P>
<P>
Since Albania and Italy signed an anti-smuggling agreement late
last year, the two Adriatic countries have cooperated in cracking
down on smuggling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
