<HEADLINE> Anhui Reports Good Farm Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 14 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
reported a good farm harvest last year, official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Official figures indicate that Anhui's grain output was up 5.6
percent to 28.5 billion kg in 1997, while its output of
oil-bearing crops rose 10 percent to 1.95 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Also last year Anhui produced 2.6 million tons of meat, 1.3
million tons of aquatic products and 301,000 tons of cotton.
</P>
<P>
A provincial official in charge of agriculture said that the
grain output of Anhui has maintained at above 25 billion kg in
four of the five years since 1993. During the period Anhui's
output of aquatic products and meat also exceeded the hallmarks of
one million and two million tons, respectively.
</P>
<P>
This indicates that Anhui's comprehensive agricultural
production capacity has reached a new level, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Anhui is a main agricultural province of China with 64 million
mu (about four million ha) of farmland. Its fiscal investment in
agriculture has totaled 7.68 billion yuan since 1993, up an
average 23 percent each year.  
</P>
