<HEADLINE> Finland's Exports to Southeast Asia Surge </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Finland's export to Southeast
Asian countries increased by 28 percent in 1997 compared with
1996, say statistics released by Finland Customs.
</P>
<P>
In the first 10 months of 1997, Finland exported 10.7 billion
Finish marks (about 1.8 billion U.S. dollars) worth of commodities
and services to Hong Kong, Indonesia, Thailand, Singapore,
Malaysia, and other major trading partners in the region. Exports
to Southeast Asia in the first 10 months of 1997 equalled the
whole export volume of 1996 to that region.
</P>
<P>
Finland's exports to the region accounted for 6.2 percent of
its total exports, compared with one percent 10 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Its major export to Southeast Asia include machinery,
electrical products and transport equipment.
</P>
<P>
But Finland Customs predicted that the current Southeast Asian
financial crisis would cripple its exports to the region,
especially in machinery and electrical products. 
</P>
