<HEADLINE> Fujian Reports 14 Percent Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, January 14 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
reported an estimated 300 billion yuan in gross domestic product
last year, up 14 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
China's national gross domestic product grew 8.8 percent in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Fujian's agricultural output
value was up nearly 10 percent to 99.5 billion yuan in 1997 while
its industrial output value surged 16.3 percent to 183.5 billion
yuan in the first 11 months.
</P>
<P>
Fujian's investment in fixed assets by state-owned units
totaled 41.7 billion yuan between January-November, up 24.6
percent over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months of last year, Fujian's retail sales of
consumer goods were worth 88.9 billion yuan, a rise of 18.5
percent year-on-year. Fujian's 11-month foreign trade volume grew
by 19.6 percent to 17.76 billion US dollars, with the year-round
figure expected to hit 11.5 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The provincial statistics bureau said in a report that Fujian's
economy is good overall, but some problems and contradictions
exist, such as low economic efficiency and poor performance of
some state-owned enterprises. 
