<HEADLINE> Fiscal Revenue of Anhui up 24.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 14 (Xinhua) -- The fiscal revenue of east
China's Anhui Province surged 24.2 percent to 24 billion yuan
(about three billion US dollars) last year, official statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
Official figures indicate that Anhui's fiscal revenue
quadrupled during the five years since 1993. The proportion of
fiscal revenue to provincial gross domestic product has increased
over the years.
</P>
<P>
As a result of growing fiscal revenues, the per capita salary
of average workers in Anhui rose from 2,869 yuan in 1993 to 5,585
yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Over the last five years, Anhui has raised more than one
billion yuan for poverty reduction. The share of fiscal funds
allocated for construction was up from 19.9 percent in 1993 to
26.4 percent in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
