<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fruit Fly Wreaks Havoc To Peru's Fruit Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The fruit fly damages 30 percent
of fruit production in Peru, causing annual losses of 100 million
U.S. dollars to farmers.
</P>
<P>
The plague harms Peru's fruit exportation because other
countries are banning the imports from Peru, according to the
Chairman of Peru Foundation, Fernando Cilloniz, quoted on Tuesday
by the local press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Cilloniz said that most citrus products are being damaged by
the fly, which resides inside the fruit and rots it.
</P>
<P>
The fly, at its larval phase, can be fought while being
inside the fruit through thermic of "freezing" treatments, but
such procedures also damage the products, he added.
</P>
<P>
"Peru is undergoing a process of extermination of the fruit
fly, with rather uneven success depending on the region of the
country where treatments are applied", Cilloniz stated.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that Peru wishes to succeed in getting rid of the
plague thanks to a program called "Citrus Survey", launched more
than two years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
