<HEADLINE> Austrian Krassnig Wins Snowboard Giant Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Dieter Krassnig of Austria had
his perfect runs to win the snowboard World Cup giant slalom in
Lienz on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Krassnig run through 37 gates down Mt Zettersfeld in one minute
52.36 seconds, establishing himself as a top contender for the
Winter Olympics next month where snowboard will make its debut in
the Olympic Games in Nagano, Japan.
</P>
<P>
Ross Rebagliatti of Canada was second in 1:54.99. Ian Price of
the United States finished third in 1:55.05. Fourth was Matthieu
Bozzetto of France with a time of 1:55.29.
</P>
<P>
In the women's race, Karine Ruby of France won her seventh
giant slalom this season, clocking 2:13.87.
</P>
<P>
Steffi von Siebenthal of Switzerland and Lidia Trettel of Italy
tied for second place with a time of 2:14.99. 
