<HEADLINE> El Nino Hardens Drought In Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A drought reinforced by the El
Nino phenomenon will prompt limited-water supply for the coming
months in Costa Rica's capital of San Jose, authorities said here
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chairman of the Costa Rican Institute of Water Supply and
Sewage System, Ana Gabriela Ross, said the city's water reserves
are at a very low level.
</P>
<P>
Between November and March, San Jose endures a rainless season
which affects the central area of the country, but this year the
El Nino phenomenon has hardened the lack of water.
</P>
<P>
"People have not yet understood how serious the problem is" and
over the last days consumption of water has increased all over the
city, Ross said.
</P>
<P>
"If consumers do not collaborate in saving water, we will have
to put into place a tight rationing", she asserted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
