<HEADLINE> Two Killed in Plane Crash at Houston </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A twin-engine jet crashed
near the George Bush International Airport at Houston today,
killing the pilot and co-pilot.
</P>
<P>
The Lear Jet was flying from Hobby Airport on the southeast
side of Houston to Bush on the north side. The jet disappeared
from radar about 9:22 a.m. EST.
</P>
<P>
In a search, the wreckage of the plane was located in a wooded
area near the airport. 
