<HEADLINE> Clinton, Blair to Meet in Washington Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 13 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony
Blair will pay an official visit to the United States on February
4-7 and meet U.S. President Bill Clinton, the White House
spokesman Mike McCurry said today.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will discuss a host of bilateral and global
issues, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that Britain holds the presidency of the
European Union and Blair is currently chairman of the G-8, so "for
Prime Minister Blair, this (visit) is something of a hat trick."
</P>
